text: Aulorhamphus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived from the early to middle Eocene. It's assigned to the Gasterosteoidei in the order Scorpaeniformes. == Related pages == * Aspidorhynchus * Balistomorphus * List of prehistoric bony fish genera == References == # "Gasterosteiformes".
